   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_6931_1816_09_04_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="Id_where"/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworthstown</placeName>
                  <date when="1816-09-04">4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> September 1816</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrinE1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Brinkley</persName>
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
               Both <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Edgeworth</persName> and I feel<lb/>
               great pleasure at the thought of seeing you<lb/>
               and your family <unclear>and</unclear> feel much obliged by<lb/>
               you kind recollection of your promise -<lb/>
               We shall therefore expect to see you and the <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrinJ1">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
               </persName>
               <lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrinS1">Miss Brinkley</persName> and my friend <persName ref="./Personography.xml#JohnX2">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Johns</persName> on Thursday<lb/>
               <del/> the 12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> and I hope the <persName ref="./Personography.xml#PondJ1">Astronomer Royal</persName>
               <lb/>
               will use his power over the clouds to procure us<lb/>
               better weather than we now have<lb/>
               As <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Edgeworth</persName> and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria</persName> both write<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               I will not any longer encroach on your<lb/>
               time dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrinE1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Brinkley</persName> but assure you<lb/>
               of the sincere regard of your obliged<lb/>
               &amp; affectionate <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">F. E</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>
                  My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrinE1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Brinkley</persName> I have only to<lb/>
                  say - Joy! - Joy! &amp; thanks for your<lb/>
                  affectionate letter and substantial good news<lb/>
                  Yours with grateful<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
                  <lb/>
                  regard<lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>Sunday</addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrinE1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> B.</persName> this letter was</addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>omitted in a packet sent to the</addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>Castle on Thursday - let me hear</addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>from you whether we shall see you</addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>on Wednesday or Thursday</addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>1816 <del/>
                  </addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrinE1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Brinkley</persName>
                  </addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dunsink-Observatory_IE">Observatory</placeName>
                  </addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>near <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName>
                  </addrLine>
                  <lb/>
               </address>
            </closer>
         </div>
